The local health officer for Prince George's County shall include in the Program operating procedures measures to collect the following data:
The number of participants served by the Program;
The length of time a participant is served by the Program;
Demographic profiles of participants served by the Program that include:
Age;
Sex;
Race;
Occupation;
Zip code of residence;
Types of drugs used;
Length of drug use; and
Frequency of injection;
The number of hypodermic needles and syringes exchanged; and
The number of participants entering drug counseling and treatment.

With the advice of the advisory committee, the local health officer for Prince George's County shall develop and implement a plan for Program evaluation as appropriate based on the prevailing knowledge at the time. The plan may include:
Reported changes in the level of drug use among Program participants;
Reported changes in the level of needle-sharing among Program participants;
Reported changes in the use of condoms among Program participants; and
The advisability of continuing the Program.
